/**
\page build_instructions Build Instructions

There is an example IOC in the support module, that demonstrates how to build an IOC that uses it. There is also a scrip that will launch a GUI.

**/

/**
\page user_manual User Manual

\section epics_user_guide How to use the EPICS software

\subsection main_screen The main top level GUI

The main EPICS user interface screen for the Lakeshore displays the 
temperature and raw voltage readbacks. There are two buttons that link
to screens that enable control of the commonly needed PID loop 1 and loop 2 parameters.

For detailed instructions on each parameter, see the Lakeshore user manual,
which can be found at the bottom of this page: \ref link_outside

\subsection setparameters The parameters set/read by EPICS

<table border="1">
<tr>
<td><b>PV</b></td>
<td><b>Name</b></td>
<td><b>Description</b></td>
<td><b>Read Only</b></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td><i>beamline</i>:KRDG0</td>
<td>Channel A Temperature</td>
<td>Read temperature on channel A in kelvin</td>
<td>Yes</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td><i>beamline</i>:KRDG1</td>
<td>Channel B Temperature</td>
<td>Read temperature on channel B in kelvin</td>
<td>Yes</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td><i>beamline</i>:KRDG2</td>
<td>Channel C Temperature</td>
<td>Read temperature on channel C in kelvin</td>
<td>Yes</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td><i>beamline</i>:KRDG3</td>
<td>Channel D Temperature</td>
<td>Read temperature on channel D in kelvin</td>
<td>Yes</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td><i>beamline</i>:SRDG0</td>
<td>Channel A Voltage</td>
<td>Read voltage on channel A</td>
<td>Yes</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td><i>beamline</i>:SRDG1</td>
<td>Channel B Voltage</td>
<td>Read voltage on channel B</td>
<td>Yes</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td><i>beamline</i>:SRDG2</td>
<td>Channel C Voltage</td>
<td>Read voltage on channel C</td>
<td>Yes</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td><i>beamline</i>:SRDG3</td>
<td>Channel D Voltage</td>
<td>Read voltage on channel D</td>
<td>Yes</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td><i>beamline</i>:ID</td>
<td>Device ID</td>
<td>Device ID string *IDN?</td>
<td>Yes</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td><i>beamline</i>:FIRMWARE:VERSION</td>
<td>Firmware Version</td>
<td>Device firmware version parsed from the identification string</td>
<td>Yes</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td><i>beamline</i>:DISABLE</td>
<td>Disable Comms</td>
<td>Stop EPICS from setting or reading parameters. 0=Enabled, 1=Disabled</td>
<td>No</td>
</tr>
</table> 

The following parameters are control loop dependent. The <i>loop</i> is either 1 or 2, meaning
control loop 1 or control loop 2.

Set parameters:

<table border="1">
<tr>
<td><b>PV</b></td>
<td><b>Name</b></td>
<td><b>Description</b></td>
<td><b>Read Only</b></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td><i>beamline</i>:SETP_S<i>loop</i></td>
<td>Setpoint</td>
<td>Set the desired temperature set point.</td>
<td>No</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td><i>beamline</i>:RANGE_S<i>loop</i></td>
<td>Heater range</td>
<td>Set the heater range. 0=Off, 1=Low, 2=Medium, 3=High</td>
<td>No</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td><i>beamline</i>:RAMP_S<i>loop</i></td>
<td>Ramprate</td>
<td>Set the temperature ramp rate.</td>
<td>No</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td><i>beamline</i>:RAMPST_S<i>loop</i></td>
<td>Ramp Status</td>
<td>Turn the ramp on or off. 0=Off, 1=On</td>
<td>No</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td><i>beamline</i>:MOUT_S<i>loop</i></td>
<td>Manual Output</td>
<td>In open loop mode, set the manual power output (in percentage of max power).</td>
<td>No</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td><i>beamline</i>:P_S<i>loop</i></td>
<td>Proportional Gain</td>
<td>Set the proportional gain.</td>
<td>No</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td><i>beamline</i>:I_S<i>loop</i></td>
<td>Integral Gain</td>
<td>Set the integral gain.</td>
<td>No</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td><i>beamline</i>:D_S<i>loop</i></td>
<td>Derivative Gain</td>
<td>Set the derivative gain.</td>
<td>No</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td><i>beamline</i>:OMMODE_S<i>loop</i></td>
<td>Control loop mode</td>
<td>Set the control loop mode. 0=Off, 1=PID, 2=Zone, 3=Open loop, 4=Monitor out, 5=Warmup supply.</td>
<td>No</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td><i>beamline</i>:OMINPUT_S<i>loop</i></td>
<td>Control loop input</td>
<td>Set the sensor input to this control loop.</td>
<td>No</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td><i>beamline</i>:OMPE_S<i>loop</i></td>
<td>Control loop power up enable</td>
<td>Set the power up enable mode of this control loop. The control loop will output power at power up if this is enabled.</td>
<td>No</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td><i>beamline</i>:TUNEMODE_S<i>loop</i></td>
<td>Auto tune mode</td>
<td>Set the mode in which to operate auto tuning. 0=P Only, 1=P and I, 2=P, I and D.</td>
<td>No</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td><i>beamline</i>:TUNESTART<i>loop</i></td>
<td>Start auto tune.</td>
<td>Start an auto tune process.</td>
<td>No</td>
</tr>
</table>

Read only control loop parameters:

<table border="1">
<tr>
<td><b>PV</b></td>
<td><b>Name</b></td>
<td><b>Description</b></td>
<td><b>Read Only</b></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td><i>beamline</i>:HTR<i>loop</i></td>
<td>Heater power.</td>
<td>Read the heater power output.</td>
<td>Yes</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td><i>beamline</i>:SETP<i>loop</i></td>
<td>Current setpoint.</td>
<td>Read the current setpoint. This changes during a ramp process.</td>
<td>Yes</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td><i>beamline</i>:RANGE<i>loop</i></td>
<td>Heater range.</td>
<td>Read the heater power output range.</td>
<td>Yes</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td><i>beamline</i>:RAMP<i>loop</i></td>
<td>Ramp rate.</td>
<td>Read the ramp rate.</td>
<td>Yes</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td><i>beamline</i>:RAMPST<i>loop</i></td>
<td>Ramp status.</td>
<td>Read the ramp status. 0=Off, 1=On</td>
<td>Yes</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td><i>beamline</i>:MOUT<i>loop</i></td>
<td>Manual output.</td>
<td>Read the current manual heater output (in percent of max power)</td>
<td>Yes</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td><i>beamline</i>:P<i>loop</i></td>
<td>Proportional gain.</td>
<td>Read the proportional gain.</td>
<td>Yes</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td><i>beamline</i>:I<i>loop</i></td>
<td>Integral gain.</td>
<td>Read the integral gain.</td>
<td>Yes</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td><i>beamline</i>:D<i>loop</i></td>
<td>Derivative gain.</td>
<td>Read the derivative gain.</td>
<td>Yes</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td><i>beamline</i>:OMMODE<i>loop</i></td>
<td>Control loop mode.</td>
<td>Read the mode this control loop is in. 0=Off, 1=PID, 2=Zone, 3=Open loop, 4=Monitor out, 5=Warmup supply.</td>
<td>Yes</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td><i>beamline</i>:OMINPUT<i>loop</i></td>
<td>Control loop input.</td>
<td>Read the sensor input that this control loop is using.</td>
<td>Yes</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td><i>beamline</i>:OMPE<i>loop</i></td>
<td>Power up enable.</td>
<td>Read the control loop power up enable mode.</td>
<td>Yes</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td><i>beamline</i>:TUNEST<i>loop</i></td>
<td>Auto tuning status.</td>
<td>Read the current status and stage of the auto tuning process. There are 4 numbers. The first one is the 
tuning status (0=No tuning, 1=Active tuning). The second is the control loop being tuned (1 or 2). 
The third is the error status of the last tune (0=No error, 1=Error). The forth is the stage of the current tune, or the stage that the last tune failed (see manual for details).</td>
<td>Yes</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td><i>beamline</i>:TUNESTSUCCESS<i>loop</i></td>
<td>Auto tuning status.</td>
<td>This PV is a seperate PV representing the auto tuning error/no error in the TUNEST PV. 0=No error, 1=Error.</td>
<td>Yes</td>
</tr>
</table>

